{\pard\plain \li0\sl-304\slmult0 \ri0\nooverflow\qj{\f2\fs22 Gabor Enery features are just the absolute sum of the squares of the real and imaginary part. The feature vectors from the real and imaginary parts of the lters were combined to explore features not otherwise apparent with the Gabor lter bank. This is also known as motion energy, which is equal to the pair summation response with a phase di erence of {=}2. This quantity is de ned as follows:}\par}
}
