{\pard\plain \li0\ql{\f2\fs19 11}\par}
}\sect\sbkpage\sectd\pard\plain
\pgwsxn11900\pghsxn16838
{\*\bkmkstart page13}{\*\bkmkend page13}
\margl1440\margr1446\margt1397\margb512\marglsxn1440\margrsxn1440\cols1\colno1\colw9020
{{{\listtext{\pard\plain {\f3\fs29 5 }\tab}}\pard\plain 
\f3\fs29 \qj\fi-480\nowidctlpar\jclisttab\tx480\faauto\ls12\ilvl0\rin0\nooverflow\lin480\itap0 \sl-333\slmult0 {\plain\f3\fs29 Compiled Feature Vectors and Classi ers }\par}
}
{\pard\sl-306\slmult0\par

{\pard\plain \li0\sl-309\slmult0 \ri0\nooverflow\qj{\f2\fs21 Each of the methods of feature extraction gives rise to good separation between several classes, and each method has classes that do not separate well. This is as was expected, and was the motivation behind this project, so the task now is to combine them into the same classi ca-tion system. Two separate methods to do so were investigated. The rst, referred to as the Concatenation Method, involves concatenating together the di erent feature vectors, and then classifying using SVMs. The other method, referred to as the Hierarchical Method, involves using multiple di erent levels of SVM classi ers in a tiered structure.}\par}
}
{\pard\sl-376\slmult0\par
{{\listtext{\pard\plain {\f14\fs24 5.1 }\tab}}\pard\plain 
\f14\fs24 \qj\fi-620\nowidctlpar\jclisttab\tx620\faauto\ls13\ilvl0\rin0\nooverflow\lin620\itap0 {\plain\f14\fs24 Concatenation Method }\par}
}
{\pard\sl-243\slmult0\par

{\pard\plain \li0\sl318\slmult1 \ri0\nooverflow\qj{\f2\fs21 The concatenation method is the simpler of the two methods investigated. The feature vec-tors from each of the feature extraction methods for a given image are concatenated into one longer vector, in an arbitrary order. Principal Component Analysis is employed on these Com-piled Vectors, with two aims in mind- one, to reduce the dimensionality of the feature vectors for computational ease; and two, to extract the most meaningful dimensions of the compiled features. First, both the SIFT bag of words and the color histogram features were concatenated.}\par}
}
