{\pard\sl-243\slmult0\par

{\pard\plain \li0\sl-297\slmult0 \ri0\nooverflow\qj{\f2\fs22 The hierarchical method takes advantage of the fact that classifying using SVMs can give more than one positive result for any given image. Firstly, the feature extraction methods were sorted in order of their broadness, de ned as the average number of positive results returned for an image when classi ed using only that feature vector.}\par}
}
