{\pard\sl-193\slmult0\par

{\pard\plain \li0\sl-309\slmult0 \ri0\nooverflow\qj{\f2\fs22 In this method, the images are rst classi ed by the broadest classi er (Bag of Words). If this results in exactly one positive result, this single result is taken as the classi cation. If there are no results, classi cation is considered to have failed. If there are more than one result, the image is then classi ed by the next most narrow classi er (gabor lters), but is restricted to only the classes that were positive in the previous result. The process is repeated, and the results are treated the same. If an image is tested on the nal method (Color histograms), and the result is not a single positive output, classi cation is considered to have failed.}\par}
}
